### ===================================
### PAYMENT IDEMPOTENCY TEST SUITE
### ===================================
### This file demonstrates payment processing and idempotency handling
### in the CoreBankDemo system using HTTP requests.

### Configuration Variables
@paymentsApiUrl = http://localhost:5294
@coreBankApiUrl = http://localhost:5032
@contentType = application/json

### Test Account Numbers (Valid IBAN format)
@account1 = NL91ABNA0417164300
@account2 = NL20INGB0001234567
@account3 = NL39RABO0300065264
@invalidAccount = INVALID-ACCOUNT-123

### ===================================
### SECTION 1: BASIC PAYMENT PROCESSING
### ===================================

### 1.1 Process Payment - Without Idempotency Key
### This payment will get a system-generated payment ID
POST {{paymentsApiUrl}}/api/payments
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "fromAccount": "{{account1}}",
  "toAccount": "{{account2}}",
  "amount": 150.00,
  "currency": "EUR"
}

### 1.2 Process Payment - With Custom Idempotency Key
### Using a client-provided idempotency key for duplicate prevention
POST {{paymentsApiUrl}}/api/payments
Content-Type: {{contentType}}
Idempotency-Key: payment-2024-001

{
  "fromAccount": "{{account1}}",
  "toAccount": "{{account3}}",
  "amount": 250.00,
  "currency": "EUR"
}

### 1.3 Retry Same Payment - Demonstrates Idempotency
### This should return the same response without processing twice
POST {{paymentsApiUrl}}/api/payments
Content-Type: {{contentType}}
Idempotency-Key: payment-2024-001

{
  "fromAccount": "{{account1}}",
  "toAccount": "{{account3}}",
  "amount": 250.00,
  "currency": "EUR"
}

### ===================================
### SECTION 2: IDEMPOTENCY EDGE CASES
### ===================================

### 2.1 Same Idempotency Key, Different Amount
### This should still return the original payment (idempotency wins)
POST {{paymentsApiUrl}}/api/payments
Content-Type: {{contentType}}
Idempotency-Key: payment-2024-001

{
  "fromAccount": "{{account1}}",
  "toAccount": "{{account3}}",
  "amount": 999.99,
  "currency": "EUR"
}

### 2.2 Different Idempotency Key, Same Details
### This creates a new payment (different idempotency key)
POST {{paymentsApiUrl}}/api/payments
Content-Type: {{contentType}}
Idempotency-Key: payment-2024-002

{
  "fromAccount": "{{account1}}",
  "toAccount": "{{account3}}",
  "amount": 250.00,
  "currency": "EUR"
}

