### ===================================
### SECTION 9: DECIMAL PRECISION TESTS
### ===================================

### 9.1 Minimum Amount (0.01)
POST {{paymentsApiUrl}}/api/payments
Content-Type: {{contentType}}
Idempotency-Key: precision-test-001

{
  "fromAccount": "{{account1}}",
  "toAccount": "{{account2}}",
  "amount": 0.01,
  "currency": "EUR"
}

### 9.2 Two Decimal Places
POST {{paymentsApiUrl}}/api/payments
Content-Type: {{contentType}}
Idempotency-Key: precision-test-002

{
  "fromAccount": "{{account1}}",
  "toAccount": "{{account2}}",
  "amount": 123.45,
  "currency": "EUR"
}

### 9.3 Large Amount (Near Limit)
POST {{paymentsApiUrl}}/api/payments
Content-Type: {{contentType}}
Idempotency-Key: precision-test-003

{
  "fromAccount": "{{account1}}",
  "toAccount": "{{account2}}",
  "amount": 999999.99,
  "currency": "EUR"
}

### ===================================
### NOTES:
### ===================================
### 1. Idempotency Keys should be unique per logical operation
### 2. The system will return the same response for duplicate idempotency keys
### 3. Idempotency keys prevent duplicate payments even with network retries
### 4. Valid IBAN format is required for account numbers
### 5. Currency must be 3 uppercase letters (ISO 4217)
### 6. Amount must be between 0.01 and 1,000,000
###
### To test idempotency:
### - Run the same request multiple times with the same Idempotency-Key
### - Observe that the response is identical each time
### - Check the outbox/inbox to confirm only one transaction was processed